      "uuid": "019bfd3e-1b97-72a2-93f3-16ad95cc8d96",
      "text": " \n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nThis is a clean diagnosis. Here's the TL;DR:\n\n---\n\n**The Problem:** Voice conversations vanish into the void. Luna talks, forgets, repeat.\n\n**Root Cause:** The pipeline is *built* but **not plugged in**. All the pieces exist:\n- Scribe (Ben Franklin) \u2705\n- Librarian (The Dude) \u2705  \n- Memory Matrix (SQLite) \u2705\n- Extraction pipeline \u2705\n\nBut voice never *calls* any of it. Two missing wires:\n1. `VoiceBackend` never sets the memory callback\n2. `PersonaAdapter` doesn't trigger extraction after processing\n\n**The Fix:** ~15 lines in `persona_adapter.py`\u2014after getting a response from Director, call `engine._trigger_extraction()` for both the user message and Luna's response.\n\n---\n\n**Current state:** The 64MB `luna_engine.db` probably has data from *non-voice* paths (MCP, direct engine calls), but voice conversations are falling through the cracks.\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Apply the fix** to `persona_adapter.py`?\n2. **Check what IS in the database** to see what memories exist from other paths?\n3. **Both**?\n\nThis feels like low-hanging fruit\u2014should be a quick win.",
